position description
the director of data science will be responsible for research and development to support aig personal insurance ranging from individual auto property travel group travel health and accident to service and warranty the advanced modeling team is a group of world-class data scientist who are passionate about challenging the status quo and driving transformational change through innovation we are keen to welcome a new team member who is a proven high performer always curious and eager to learn and value an inspiring and collaborative team work environment
this position will collaborate with aig product underwriting actuarial and technology team leverage cutting edge technique including gis natural language processing deep learning and other machine learning tool to solve both classic and new challenge in an industry with a long history some example of problem we face include more accurate and efficient underwriting and pricing risk management and segmentation usage based insurance sharing economy and the impact on insurance from connected driverless car and iot
core responsibilities
provide overall leadership for analytical and modeling project
understand complex business challenge in different area underwriting pricing loss prevention customer retention claim and fraud and design practical and scalable analytics solution where applicable
design data warehouse and technical solution together with technology team to facilitate fast and efficient manipulation of large volume of data for analytics purpose
guide and supervise a team of data scientist to build predictive model using cutting edge machine learning or statistical modeling technique
communicate analytics result to business leader and cultivate a data-driven decision process
assess and make sure that project have sufficient resource and talent support identify key step milestone and deliverable develop and maintain a reasonable timeline
maintain and update standard to ass and document modeling process and performance
mentor junior team member and create training and growth opportunity
position requirements
required qualifications
advanced degree phd preferred in one or more quantitative field eg computer science physic math statistic economics computational linguistics
deep understanding of modern machine learning and statistical modeling technique eg glm gam decision tree random forest svm deep learning gbm clustering bayesian averaging
expert level skill in one or more modeling machine learning language such a python r
expertise in sql
hands on experience manipulating large volume data in modern big data environment eg hadoop spark hive etc
proven track record leading or working within a successful team in analytics and predictive modeling
excellent communication skill in particularly the ability to explain complex analytical solution to non-technical audience
capability to work within a large matrix organization with many stake holder around the globe and the ability to lead and influence decision
10+ year of experience in data science analytics or related area will be flexed for exceptional candidate
highly desired qualifications
experience and knowledge in the insurance industry property and casualty individual travel group health and accident warranty and service
proficient programming skill in one or more of these language or equivalent c++ c java php scala ruby
experience building web application a plus
hands-on cloud architecture experience aws experience a plus
experience in automation vagrant chef docker or similar
familiarity with common computing environment eg linux shell scripting
contributions to open-source project a plus
